bug.short_desc: Nested static generic class reference is incorrectly marked as compile error

long_desc.thetext: Sasi, thanks for taking a look.

Created attachment 244273 Patch with proposed fix and tests
Patch with proposed fix and tests

Attached patch with proposed fix and tests. When type arguments are present in a qualified type reference, we correctly check whether the qualifying type is static or not but when there are no type arguments, the error is reported with out performing the same check. Corrected that and added tests. Srikanth, please review
For the record, the bug was also present in 4.3.
Verified for 4.5 M1 with build I20140804-2000
